      <hedline>
        <hl1>Meat-Eating 'Vegetarians'</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Bettina Barbier letter says July 28 article on vegetarian diets for children suggested wrongly that one can be a vegetarian while continuing to eat chicken or fish</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>''Losing Meat, but Keeping a Child's Diet Balanced'' (July 25) used some terms that are contrary to the nature of vegetarianism. The terms pesco-vegetarian and pollo-vegetarian are of recent coinage -- by those who would claim the hip part of being vegetarian, without the fuss and bother of actually changing their diets. The idea that a person can be a vegetarian while continuing to eat meat, whether from chickens or fish, would cause the word vegetarian to lose all meaning. A chicken is not a vegetable.</p>
        <p>BETTINA BARBIER  Huntington, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
